Effect of discarded containers on animals
Project
The main aim of this project is to understand how littering affect animals. In particular, we focus on discarded containers which can serve as alternative microhabitat or constitute deadly trap.
View
Dermestidae
Project
View
Study of the immatures stages of skin beetles (Coleoptera: Dermestidae)
Project
The main aim of the project is to broaden our knowledge of the immature stages of Dermestidae including their morphology, biology, ecology, anatomy and physiology. The current level of recognition and understanding of the above is less than sufficient. Only 10% of more than 1600 described species have any reference to the immatures stages; each new study on the larvae and pupae will help to fill this gap. As a result, I would be most grateful to anybody who could support this research by sending me larvae, larval skins (exuviae) and pupae of known species. Further information on the biology and behaviour of these immature stages, including interactions with other species, would be most welcome. I can be contacted at: marcin.kadej@uwr.edu.pl
